---

## Why This Design is Better

| Aspect | Old | New |
|--------|-----|-----|
| **Scoring Speed** | 7+ steps, blocked on context setup | 2 clicks minimal, optional tagging |
| **Flexibility** | Must match exact event category | Fuzzy matching catches typos |
| **Helpers** | See admin complexity | See only what they need |
| **Events** | Fixed nested structure | Flat tags with smart matching |
| **Defaults** | None - must configure | Auto-creates minimal context |

---

## Key Files Modified

- `web/control/control.js`: Fuzzy matching + context logic (lines 504-573, line 1733)
- `web/control/index.html`: Simplified form HTML (lines 63-124)
- `web/control/control.css`: Form & tag styles (lines 1614-1705)

---

## Data Flow Example

**Before Fix:**
```
User clicks button → "Start event context first!" → Cannot proceed → Blocked
```

**After Fix:**
```
User clicks button → Points added with default context → Auto-tagged if tag set → Done
```

---

**Note**: This is a breaking change in philosophy (event no longer a gate), but it's backward-compatible with existing data. All old points still work fine.
